title: Lieke van Wijk
text:
Lieke van Wijk (born 18 September 1993) is a Dutch <a href="field%20hockey">field hockey</a> player.
Playing for Netherlands junior teams for 4 years, van Wijk won 4 gold medals; two EuroHockey Junior Nations Championships, one <a href="Youth%20Olympic%20Games">Youth Olympic Games</a> and one <a href="Women%27s%20Hockey%20Junior%20World%20Cup">Junior World Cup</a>.
Lieke van Wijk also plays at an international level for the <a href="Netherlands%20women%27s%20national%20field%20hockey%20team">Netherlands</a> Indoor hockey team. With the team, she won gold at the <a href="2016%20Women%27s%20EuroHockey%20Indoor%20Nations%20Championship">2016 EuroHockey Indoor Championship</a> and silver at the <a href="2018%20Women%27s%20Indoor%20Hockey%20World%20Cup">2018 Indoor Hockey World Cup</a>.
